{
  "stem": "24195.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she became an ally of my-- all of my, my mother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she, she was forceful in dealing with this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so our situation improved somewhat, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had-- we could find another apartment that-- more to our life-- you know, standard of living.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we didn't have to stay in the-- in the-- no longer in, in the clinic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- that was-- that was the period of one-- the end of one period there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'd like to mention one more thing, though.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There are-- there was always an undercurrent of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe not just an undercurrent, maybe it was more of an-- a very obvious symptom in, in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the-- long before Hitler took over, it might have not been during the Kaiser's-- I mean, I mean, you know, up to the period of World War I.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I think it developed because a lot of the terrible times after-- the hard times-- economic-- hard economic times after World War I, in that period of what they called the Weimar Republic.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, I, I believe a lot of Germans felt that the Jewish people had something that they, you know, they were doing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they were doing better.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most of the Jews in Germany did well, you know, and all-- very prominent in all walks of life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that they would-- that that might have been accountable for or contributing to the misery of some of the economic miseries of some of the German people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was always a current of anti-Semitism in, in Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think it was very well-- very well expressed in one incident that my mother always told me.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
